-- ISE says in advanced talks with Deutsche Boerse
-- 
-- Mon Apr 30, 2007 9:49am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/30/us-ise-deutscheboerse-talks-idUSWNAS858320070430

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Equity options market International Securities Exchange Holdings Inc. ISE.N said on Monday it is in advanced talks with Deutsche Boerse that could lead to a deal with Eurex, the global derivatives platform that Deutsche Boerse co-owns with Swiss exchange SWX. 

 Deutsche Boerse ( DB1Gn.DE ) said on Monday it plans to offer $2.8 billion for ISE to expand in fast-growing options trading.